```

**Issue 2: postinstall.js doesn't copy hooks/lib/ directory**
File: claude-dev-toolkit/scripts/postinstall.js (lines 179-197)
The copySelectedHooks() function only copies top-level .sh files. The hooks/lib/ subdirectory (containing argument-parser.sh, config-constants.sh, context-manager.sh, error-handler.sh, execution-engine.sh, file-utils.sh, subagent-discovery.sh, subagent-validator.sh) is NOT copied.

Fix: Add logic to copySelectedHooks() to also copy the lib/ subdirectory:
```javascript
// After the existing loop, copy lib/ directory if it exists
const libSourceDir = path.join(sourceDir, 'lib');
const libTargetDir = path.join(targetDir, 'lib');
if (fs.existsSync(libSourceDir)) {
    if (!fs.existsSync(libTargetDir)) {
        fs.mkdirSync(libTargetDir, { recursive: true });
    }
    const libFiles = fs.readdirSync(libSourceDir);
    for (const libFile of libFiles) {
        const libSource = path.join(libSourceDir, libFile);
        const libTarget = path.join(libTargetDir, libFile);
        if (fs.statSync(libSource).isFile()) {
            fs.copyFileSync(libSource, libTarget);
            if (libFile.endsWith('.sh')) {
                fs.chmodSync(libTarget, '755');
            }
            console.log('  Installed hook lib: ' + libFile);
        }
    }
}
```

